SIMPLE: underbear
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underbear
<hw>Un`der*bear"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>underberan</ets>. See <er>Under</er>, and <er>Bear</er> to
support.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To support; to endure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To line; to guard; to face; <as>as, cloth of gold
<ex>underborne</ex> with blue tinsel</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underbearer</ent>⟦br⟧
